   <body>
      <context>
         <p>You must have <xref href="../marking-clauses_45220111_45220111/45220111.xml" format="dita">marked static text in the agreement document as a clause</xref> in the same session using Playbook. Unmarking a clause removes Apttus clause properties and returns the text to a static state.</p>
      </context>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Go to <menucascade>
                  <uicontrol>Document </uicontrol>
                  <uicontrol>Clauses</uicontrol>
               </menucascade>.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p> Click on the clause name in the list. </p>
            <stepresult>
               <p>The document scrolls to highlight the selected clause.</p>
               <fig id="fig_hmt_fw4_12c">
                  <image height="250"
                         placement="break"
                         width="773"
                         href="../attachments/45220112/49086821.png"
                         id="image_imt_fw4_12c"/>
               </fig>
            </stepresult>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click the <image placement="inline"
                      width="20"
                      href="../attachments/45220112/49086822.png"
                      id="image_hkh_hw4_12c"/>
               <uicontrol>unMark </uicontrol>icon. </p>
            <stepresult>
               <p>The Panel refreshes and the clause no longer appears in the list. The clause
                  boundary is removed from the marked text and it returns to its previous state.</p>
            </stepresult>
         </li>
      </ol>
   </body>
